wikipedia_page.main: William Strickland, 6th Baron Boynton, esq. (February 18, 1753 – January 8, 1834) was an 18th-century gentleman farmer and writer from Yorkshire, England. He was the eldest son of Sir George Strickland of York, England, from the ancient English Strickland family of Sizergh. He established his own farm at Welburn in York and, in 1808, succeeded his father as the sixth baron of Boynton.
